  "response": "This is a straightforward inclusion-exclusion count:\n\n**Step 1: Count multiples of 3 from 1 to 1000.**\n⌊1000/3⌋ = 333\n\n**Step 2: Count multiples of 5 from 1 to 1000.**\n⌊1000/5⌋ = 200\n\n**Step 3: Count multiples of 15 (divisible by both 3 and 5).**\n⌊1000/15⌋ = 66\n\n**Step 4: Count numbers divisible by 3 or 5.**\nBy inclusion-exclusion: 333 + 200 − 66 = 467\n\n**Step 5: Exclude the multiples of 15.**\nNumbers divisible by 3 or 5 but not by 15: 467 − 66 = 401\n\n(Sanity check: multiples of 3 but not 15 = 333 − 66 = 267; multiples of 5 but not 15 = 200 − 66 = 134; these sets are disjoint, and 267 + 134 = 401. ✓)\n\nANSWER: 401",
